messages.message: Who owns the `continuous-integration/jenkins/pr-merge` bot in github? My revert is failing because it's trying to pull from `null/instabase` instead of `instabase/instabase` https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/17532
That one won’t block you from merging. Once the Travis one passes, you should be set.

I think the problem is - The PR you created is not from any instabase fork rather it’s from the `instabase/instabase` repo itself.

The pipeline expects CHANGE_FORK env variable which in this particular case is `null`

I’m adding a fallback for CHANGE_FORK to default to `instabase/instabase` if the value is `null`
